  {
    "id": "sternCitationsCriticality2024",
    "abstract": "Many court systems are overwhelmed all over the world, leading to huge backlogs of pending cases. Effective triage systems could ensure proper prioritization of open cases. We introduce the Criticality Prediction dataset for Swiss Federal Supreme Court decisions, featuring a two-tier labeling system: (1) the binary LD-Label identifying cases published as Leading Decisions, and (2) the Citation-Label ranking cases by citation frequency and recency. Analysis shows that over 96% of BGer decisions are non-critical (never published as Leading Decisions), while a small fraction of decisions accumulate the vast majority of citations.",
